This recipe has become a standard cocktail party appetizer for us...a real crowd pleaser.

Rating: 3
I'm happy to find the arugula recipes. This one is wonderful for snacks with wine/drinks. I sow it and it grows like a weed. Don't pull them up: just cut off the leaves -- they grow out again. A wonderful addition to green salad. (It's somewhere between herb and salad green!)

Rating: 3
This was a pretty good Crostini recipe. Don't leave out the butter - I tried it both ways, and it's pretty dry and dull without. I would make this again if I were making an assortment of Bruschetta, but there are other recipes that I love more (Bruschetta with White Beans, Tomatoes and Olives from this site is fabulous.) Contrary to other reviewers, I would use a stronger bleu next time.

Rating: 3
Very good and easy to make. I took it to a party and it was a big hit. Be sure to use the milder gorgonzola cheese, though. I used some blue cheese I had on hand and the results were overpowering.

Rating: 3
I enjoyed this recipe but for my oven and taste the inital baking time for the bread should have been 5-10 min. Also I servered them as per the recipe and the second batch I added a thin slice of cherry tomatoe on top just after I took them out of the oven, and my company liked this addition but said it was fine without the tomatoe .

Rating: 4
These are delicious. They are a big hit at parties and I like that you can do most of the prep in advance. Must try if you like blue cheese. Also I had never had aragula before. It's a wonderful herb!